{"author":{"id":"ae525fbc43b154bc9bc99bfaa6c122845b528404c0dfd51da410d6b5056ce29c"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1751914178,"nonce":"iI5UIsweR8GU9o0xGPYbcpLAMvc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s6_VAPb","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7120","origin":"github"},"title":"metaSpades only does co-assembly on collections","message":"Hi,\n\nI've been trying to pass a paired collection of samples to metaSpades, and cannot figure out how _not_ to get a co-assembly. It seems as if by default, all samples are co-assembled and the only way to assemble samples separately is to call metaspades once per sample, which is not very practical with a few dozen samples. \n\nI would have expected the collection mode to be a batch mode by default, triggering one job per pair. This is what MEGAHIT does on galaxy, with the option to switch on co-assembly if one wants to pool all samples.\n\nGiven that co-assembly is a very specific type of assembly that most people don't do because it doesn't always make biological sense, would it be possible to \n- enable batch mode with collections\n- make an optional co-assembly switch\n?\n\nThank you","files":null}]}